    "In the absence of standardized data management procedures, maintaining accurate and comprehensive records becomes challenging, hindering the reproducibility of studies and traceability of sample characteristics.",
    "Ethical and legal compliance faces hurdles due to the absence of uniform guidelines, leading to uncertainties in obtaining informed consent and ensuring participant privacy.",
    "Quality control and assurance suffer when standard measures are lacking, risking issues such as contamination and mislabeling.",
    "The accessibility and sharing of samples are impeded without standardized practices, hindering global collaborations.",
    "Long-term storage conditions and data format standardization become critical for sample stability and integration of diverse datasets, respectively."
